<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n54140g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54140g">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54140g"> 140(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> did woodman spare / He did. Th. G.</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Henry Russel, who composed the melody <font color="green">[of &lsquo;Woodman, Spare that Tree&rsquo;]</font>, has left us this touching story, to prove the power of the words and music: &lsquo;After I had sung the noble ballad of <i>Woodman, Spare that Tree</i>, at Boulogne, an old gentleman among the audience, who was greatly moved by the simple and touching beauty of the words, rose and said, &ldquo;I beg your pardon, Mr. Russell, but <mark>was the tree really spared</mark>?&rdquo; &ldquo;<mark>It was</mark>,&rdquo; said I. &ldquo;<mark>I am very glad to hear it</mark>,&rdquo; said he, as he took his seat among the applause of the whole assembly.&rdquo; <small> Sigmund Spaeth, <a name="REAW2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#REAW2"><cite title="source">Read 'Em and Weep</cite></a> (1935) 23</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Joyce&apos;s &lsquo;Thank God&rsquo;. </mm> </dd></dl>
